About FW Frost Engineers

Being one of the largest Sub-Contract Engineering Company's in Norfolk, F.W.Frost Engineers Ltd is still a family-owned and run business based in Norwich, employing a loyal workforce of nearly 40 people, specialising in the manufacture of quality fabrications and machined components, dealing in bespoke, specialist equipment and sub-contract work, rather than a standard product.

Having recently celebrated being over 78 years in business, the company is still going from strength to strength with a client base that is expanding.

What We Do

Fabrication

We have strong team of skilled welders and fabricators allowing us to work in sheet-metal and upto heavy plate in materials like Aluminium, Mild Steel and Stainless Steel

Our Fabrication Capabilities

Machining

Having wide range of both manual and CNC mills and lathes gives us the capacity to cover most aspects of precision engineering, backed up with two large horizontal borers there aren't many areas of machining we cannot cover.

Our Machining Capabilities

Contact Us

Quality Work

Experience across food, motor, chemical, water, agriculture, and subsea industries showcases our consistently high-quality machining and fabrication. Supported by coded welding and a robust quality control system, our reputation for excellence is truly worldwide

Working on this varied range of products has given us much experience of high-quality work, giving us a reputation to be proud of.

Philosophy & Ethos

Upholding a philosophy of quality and service, we continually invest in the latest CNC and CAM technologies, blended with traditional engineering expertise. This ensures our manufacturing processes are optimized, guaranteeing high-quality outcomes for every customer.

Work Methods

Providing quality service means being adaptable. Our flexible methods allow us to swiftly meet customer requirements and partner in development, ensuring cost-effective solutions delivered reliably and on time.

Complete Solutions

As well as providing a high quality manufacturing service, we can also manage a complete project from design, with our own 2D & 3D CAD facility, through to coatings and treatments, assembly and on-site installation.

Agriculture

From simple rollers to complete fabricated chassis, we have built them all. Our skilled engineers are capable of completing any project.

Confectionery

From custom machinery to equipment repairs, we support confectionery manufacturers with precision engineering to keep production lines running smoothly.

Chemical

Trusted partner for chemical industry needs, providing expert machining and fabrication services for complex and critical applications.

Defence

Working on high tolerance fabrications and machined components is all in a days work for our skilled engineering team.

Motor-sport

Harnessing advanced machining and fabrication techniques, we engineer performance components for motor-sport, from classic to modern.

Packaging

Our team designs and manufactures bespoke machinery used in the packaging industry, optimising production efficiency and reliability.

Water

From helping with environmental protection to simple pipework our engineers can be relied on for a solid solution.
